<h1 id="jeikeio-brand-design-brief">JEIKEio Brand &amp; Design Brief</h1>
<h2 id="purpose">Purpose</h2>
<p>JEIKEio (Access Management System) is a secure, enterprise-grade platform for managing user access to systems and privileges. It streamlines access requests, approvals, and auditing with flexible deployment options (SaaS or standalone).</p>
<h2 id="audience">Audience</h2>
<ul>
<li>All company employees who request access</li>
<li>IT administrators and security teams</li>
<li>System owners and supervisors</li>
<li>Compliance and audit stakeholders</li>
<li>Internal developers/ops teams</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="product-summary">Product Summary</h2>
<p>JEIKEio centralizes access control workflows for the entire organization:</p>
<ul>
<li>Employees request access to systems/privileges</li>
<li>Supervisors and system owners approve</li>
<li>Automated provisioning and audit logging</li>
<li>Configurable workflows and integrations</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="core-values">Core Values</h2>
<ul>
<li>Security-first</li>
<li>Transparency &amp; auditability</li>
<li>Operational efficiency</li>
<li>Trust and accountability</li>
<li>Scalability for growing organizations</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="key-differentiators">Key Differentiators</h2>
<ul>
<li>Workflow-driven access lifecycle</li>
<li>Built-in audit logging and compliance readiness</li>
<li>Flexible deployment: SaaS or standalone</li>
<li>Integrations with external systems</li>
<li>Strong security hardening (CSRF, headers, rate limiting, account lockout)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="brand-personality">Brand Personality</h2>
<ul>
<li>Professional, dependable, and precise</li>
<li>Calm and authoritative</li>
<li>Modern, clean, and minimal</li>
<li>Emphasis on trust and compliance</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="tone-of-voice">Tone of Voice</h2>
<ul>
<li>Clear and concise</li>
<li>Security-aware and responsible</li>
<li>Action-oriented (approve, review, audit)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="visual-direction">Visual Direction</h2>
<h3 id="visual-themes">Visual Themes</h3>
<ul>
<li>“Secure gateway” and “verified access” motifs</li>
<li>Subtle references to shields, keys, checks, and audit trails</li>
<li>Balanced tech + enterprise aesthetic</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="style-preferences">Style Preferences</h3>
<ul>
<li>Minimal, clean UI</li>
<li>High contrast for readability</li>
<li>Consistent spacing and alignment</li>
<li>Subtle gradients or flat design (either is acceptable)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="color-guidance-conceptual-">Color Guidance (Conceptual)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Primary: Deep navy / dark blue (trust, security)</li>
<li>Secondary: Teal or green (approval/success)</li>
<li>Neutrals: Light gray, charcoal</li>
<li>Accent: Amber/orange for warnings or pending states</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="typography-guidance-conceptual-">Typography Guidance (Conceptual)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Primary: Modern sans-serif (e.g., Inter, Source Sans, or similar)</li>
<li>Secondary: Monospace or semi-condensed for technical labels (optional)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="logo-guidance">Logo Guidance</h2>
<ul>
<li>Should work at small sizes (app icon, favicon)</li>
<li>Avoid overly complex details</li>
<li>Consider abstract “access” or “permission” concepts</li>
<li>Maintain recognizability in monochrome</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="usage-contexts">Usage Contexts</h2>
<ul>
<li>Web application UI</li>
<li>Documentation and admin guides</li>
<li>Email notifications</li>
<li>Security and compliance reports</li>
<li>Marketing site or product sheets</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="deliverables-requested">Deliverables Requested</h2>
<ul>
<li>Logo design</li>
<li>Logo usage guidelines</li>
<li>Color palette</li>
<li>Typography guidelines</li>
<li>Iconography</li>
<li>Do&#39;s and don&#39;ts</li>
<li>Brand book design</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="do-don-t">Do / Don’t</h2>
<h3 id="do">Do</h3>
<ul>
<li>Emphasize clarity and trust</li>
<li>Use consistent, professional visual language</li>
<li>Keep layouts structured and readable</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="don-t">Don’t</h3>
<ul>
<li>Use playful or casual styling</li>
<li>Overuse gradients or heavy shadows</li>
<li>Use ambiguous security signals</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="suggested-taglines-optional-">Suggested Taglines (Optional)</h2>
<ul>
<li>“Trusted access, verified.”</li>
<li>“Secure approvals, clear audit trails.”</li>
<li>“Access governance made simple.”</li>
</ul>
